"n.纱线 【考】 knit : yarn / plait : hair(编织纱线/编辫头发) 【记】 注意不要和yawn(打呵 欠)相混 n. 纱线(用于纺织或编织) 【区】yawn(v 打呵欠) 【类】knit: yarn = plait: hair 编织纱线 = 编头发 【记】音：羊，羊毛纱线；darn织补 用yarn 【相关】yawn 打呵欠(象是打呵欠的声音；音：仰，仰起来打呵欠) yarn (n.)  Old English gearn ""spun fiber, spun wool,"" from Proto-Germanic *garnan (cognates: Old Norse, Old High German, German garn, Middle Dutch gaern, Dutch garen ""yarn""), from PIE root *ghere- ""intestine, gut, entrail"" (cognates: Old Norse gorn ""gut,"" Sanskrit hira ""vein; entrails,"" Latin hernia ""rupture,"" Greek khorde ""intestine, gut-string,"" Lithuanian zarna ""gut""). The phrase to spin a yarn ""to tell a story"" is first attested 1812, from a sailors' expression, on notion of telling stories while engaged in sedentary work such as yarn-twisting."
